<paragraph blockId="17.[816,1429,388,515]" pageId="17" pageNumber="329">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons" box="[1039,1248,422,448]" firstAuthor="Simmons" pageId="17" pageNumber="329" refId="ref14567" refString="SIMMONS, N. B. 2005. Order Chiroptera. Pp. 312 - 529, in Mammals species of the World (D. E. WILSON and D. M. REEDER, eds). Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, 2142 pp." type="book" year="2005">Simmons (2005)</bibRefCitation>
there are no other named forms included in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1904" box="[816,939,489,515]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="329" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nanulus">
<emphasis box="[816,939,489,515]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="329">P. nanulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
